          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " To measure an energy depended cross section the",
                "time of flight method was employed, which uses the",
                "neutron flight time between production at the",
                "spallation target and the (n,gamma)-reaction in the",
                "detector. With a flight path of 20.28 m it is",
                "possible to determine the neutron energy of a",
                "reaction. To account for the high count rates in the",
                "resonances at 28 eV and 229 eV the sample was",
                "measured twice. The 40 microA measurement reduced",
                "pile-up in those resonances while the second 100",
                "microA measurement collected enough statistics in the",
                "in regions between the resonances. Both measurements",
                "were then combined."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "To correct for effects of scattering and absorption",
                "in the sample Monte Carlo simulations were performed",
                "using the evaluated capture and elastic scatter cross",
                "sections."
              ]
            }
          ],
